April is Autism Awareness Month with April 2nd being Autism Awareness Day.

Today, like every day, we are proud to be part of a community that supports ALL students. We promote autism awareness and assure that everyONE affected by autism achieves the highest quality of life! We may see things differently but that gives us all the strength and passion in everything we do.
To show YOUR support make a sign, wear blue, or wear your apparel and send us a picture! (mpearce@wyomingcsd.org)
Here's just a few of the supporters at Wyoming CSD 💙💙💙...

Good evening everyone.

Today (3/21) a telephone message was sent out to all families with students in grades K-8.

We are researching all the details involved in sending Chromebooks home to students. We ask you to go on to the school's website (www.wyomingcsd.org) and fill out the TECHNOLOGY FORM found in the section "Helping you through the emergency closure".

The more information we receive will help us make the appropriate decisions for everyone.

Thank you.

post_text: Wyoming Basketball team falls short against the Letchworth Indians, 41-39. It was an exciting game that went back and forth throughout the night. Scoring was led by Dan with the most rebounds while Ethan, Liam and Dan were not far behind. Josh, Zak and Connor leading the team steals and Ian playing a crucial role in developing plays. Donald had his best game all season being a powerhouse on defense and leading the team in assists. Last game of the season is Saturday at 9:30 in Perry. Come on out and rally behind our team. The games are always fun to be a part of.

post_text:
On Monday the Boys Basketball team took on the Attica Blue Devils and dominated the court 36-19. Dan Santullo and Zak Gentile led the scoring for the boys while Ian Stothers and Donald Reinhart played strong on the point. Josh Merrill and Connor Hollands defended the paint keeping the offense at bay while Ethan Heineman played strong from the key leading the Wyoming charge.

Then on Tuesday the court turned on our Wyoming Indians as they lost to the Warsaw Tigers, 28-14. Wyoming still played well shutting down Warsaw in a highly contested defense. Josh and Connor controlled the tempo of the game while Donald, Ian and Zak led the team in scoring.

Next game....Thursday, 2/11 in Letchworth at 4:30.

The Ski & Snowboard Club is enjoying a great season at Swain! This years club has 10 students. We ski every Monday for 6 weeks starting on Martin Luther King, Jr. Day.

On February 15th we will have a special offer for beginners or novices. $25 to ski (or snowboard) for the entire day! A lesson, equipment and lift ticket are all included in this low rate. Contact Mrs. Cox or Mrs. Kunze at the school if you would like to go. Spread the word, we'd love to fill a bus. Come join the fun!
